This repo contains the definition of a bundle of several related ontologies called ADIRO. The ontologies are in TTL format.

The initial work started by writing a big monolith ontology called aec_drawing_ontology_v01.ttl. We then divided it into:

1. Parent/Core ontology
Minimal shared primitives and cross-module contracts:

:contains, :has
:exampleImage, :labellableRoot
Possibly very generic classes like :DrawingElement

2. Drawing metadata ontology
Sheet/layout/document structure:

:DrawingSheet, :Layout, :Metadata
:Titleblock, :Legend, :RevisionTable, :Note, :TextualNote
:DrawingType + :Plan, :Section, :Elevation, :Detail
:referstodrawingid

3. Common symbols ontology (cross-discipline layout content)
New concepts like dimensions, callouts, grids, levels, etc. (mostly reusable non-domain symbols).

4. Domain-common symbols ontologies
Shared within some domains (e.g., facade+structural).

5. Domain ontologies (discipline-specific)
Facade engineering only (for drawings related to the engineering design of the facades of buildings, the only domain our monolith covered) and other domain-specific ones that we will write in the future, like MEP engineering, structural_engineering, etc.
Example existing facade concepts: :FacadeComponent, :FacadeSystem, :DGU (Double Glazing Unit).